cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this repository in your work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Causal Inference in Oncology: TCGA Pan-Cancer Atlas"
abstract: >
  A self-contained tutorial repository demonstrating seven causal inference
  and survival analysis methods — Kaplan-Meier, Cox proportional hazards,
  propensity score matching, inverse probability weighting, difference-in-
  differences, mediation analysis, instrumental variables, and sensitivity
  analysis — applied to real clinical data from the TCGA Pan-Cancer Atlas 2018
  (6,568 patients, 19 cancer types).
authors:
